The President hosted Speaker Pelosi and Leader Schumer in the Oval Office to discuss the Build Back Better Act and the bipartisan infrastructure deal. They emphasized their commitment to the Build Back Better Act, which includes tax cuts for middle-class families, affordable healthcare and child care, and addressing climate change. They also emphasized their commitment to the bipartisan infrastructure agreement, which includes investments in roads, bridges, internet access, and clean energy. Both bills are seen as priorities and have strong support from the American people. The President has been engaging with lawmakers and his staff to further these initiatives.